September 2 at 8:58 PM ·

Starting tomorrow afternoon, we will be posting How-To videos for all aspects of virtual learning. These videos will be available on our website as well starting next week. The How-To videos will be tutorials starting with:

1) Powering on the Chromebook and logging into the computer.
2) Logging onto email
3) How to get to Google Classroom
4) How to log into Clever (the hub that houses all curriculum platforms)
5) How to access Brightspace D2L, the digital classroom where all assignments will be posted.

These videos will be step-by-step instructions for each and we will include written instructions as well.

Stay Tuned for great information to help make virtual learning easier!

#onedreamoneteam
#gospartans
💙💛

post_text:
Good morning!!!!
Just a note to let you know to expect mail soon. We have mailed out letters letting you know the assignment, Hybrid Days (A or B) or Virtual, for your child.
***If your child is an A student, he or she will come on Monday and Tuesday’s with distant learning on Wednesday, Thursday, & Friday.
***If your child is a B student, he or she will come on Thursday and Friday with distant learning on Monday, Tuesday, & Wednesday.
*** Virtual students will participate Monday - Friday in a combination of virtual lessons with direct teaching and distant learning/independent lessons. Suggested family and student schedules will be sent home with students at Virtual Pick Up
tomorrow from 9-11!

Good evening Spartan Family!
The administration is asking that if you have had a change in phone number(s), emergency contacts, or mailing address, please notify the school so that we can make those changes within our data system. We will be mailing things out and making frequent calls with important information. We don’t want you to miss out on what’s happening at Central!
We appreciate your cooperation with this and ask that you stop by to make these changes. If you can’t stop by, give us a call. 281.2130 or 281.2232
Thanks so much!

As our teachers have been calling to get your preference of learning for the upcoming school year, here is the Virtual Application for those who have said they’d rather do virtual for now.
We appreciate your input.

If you’ve not heard from us, feel free to call the school and let us know your preference of learning for the upcoming school year, face-to-face or full virtual.

Also, if you have changed phone numbers or moved since school closed, please contact the school and update your information. We appreciate your cooperation with this.

IMPORTANT ANNOUNCEMENT

Beginning this week, Grab and Go lunch and breakfasts will be Mondays and Thursdays, instead of Mondays and Wednesdays. We are happy to announce this change is because students will now be receiving meals for 7 days instead of 5. Pick-up locations will continue to be at BHS and Byrd Avenue schools. At BHS, the pick-up spot will be behind the gym and cafeteria. There will be tables set up for pick up. At Byrd Avenue, the pick-up will be in front of the school.

Superintendent Lisa Tanner

shared_text:
Steve Caparotta WAFB
March 17 at 1:27 PM ·

ATTENTION TEACHERS, PARENTS, KIDS...

I'll be hosting a series of weather lessons for kids in the coming days/weeks here on Facebook. Once completed, these will be posted on our website, likely along with at least a couple of worksheets relevant to the material I've covered.

Tomorrow's first talk will be a basic introduction to weather for younger kids...think K-4. I'll cover topics like the water cycle, thunderstorm threats and safety, tools that meteorologists use, and more.

Friday's lesson will be all about hurricanes and should appeal to a wider age group.

I will attempt to come up with some additional lessons for the coming weeks, but may also repeat some of these to give kids opportunities to engage live on Facebook with their questions.

post_text: Thank you to our 2019-2020 Teacher of the Year and her family for providing our staff with Crawfish and cake. Mrs. Vergie Moses always goes above and beyond for our students and our school. We appreciate your hospitable gesture during the teachers lunch break and providing them with delicious crawfish and a beautiful and yummy cake!

PBIS Mardi Gras Event
Thank you to the MCCA and Krewe of Unity Royalty and their entourages for coming to visit our students today! We appreciate you. The students enjoyed it so much!
We also unveiled our 2020 bead art that Ms. Vicky Evans and the 5th grade students created!

Lia Norman, 2nd Place winner Parish-wide, for ADAPT Heart Smart Essay Contest.
Lia was accompanied to an ADAPT luncheon by Mrs. Parker, her ELA teacher, and Mrs. Houston, Principal Of Central Elementary where she was honored with a medal, certificate and a $25 check.
